@database games
@version $VER: games.guide 2.3 (21.5.100)

*****************************************************************

@node MAIN "Games"
@{jcenter}@{fg highlight}Games@{fg text}
@{jleft}
I regularly test MSX games with fMSX Amiga. Of course, occasionally a change
to the system will mean that programs that used to run no longer do so, but on
the whole, the information in this section should give a good indication of
what works and what doesn't. Of course if you have any additions or spot
mistakes, please let me know!

Sometimes it can be hard to determine if a program is in fact operating
correctly. The fact that a great many MSX programs are in Japanese doesn't
help either.

The games have been divided into categories. The following categories are
available:

    @{" Disk games        " link DISKGAMES} These games fill one or more disks.
    @{" Disk-based games  " link DISKBASEDGAMES} Many of these games fit on a disk.
    @{" 16K and 32K ROMs  " link SMALLROMS}
    @{" Larger ROMs       " link MEGAROMS}
    @{" Tape-based games  " link TAPEBASEDGAMES}

The following list of games comes especially recommended!

    @{" Recommended games " link RECOMMENDED}

@endnode

*****************************************************************

@node RECOMMENDED "Recommended games"
@{jcenter}@{fg highlight}Recommended games@{fg text}
@{jleft}
@{U}RPGs@{UU}
S.D. Snatcher                     Extremely cool cyberpunk adventure.
Metal Gear 1 or 2                 Great "covert tactical operation" games.
Dragonslayer 6: Legend of Heroes  Extremely well-done Final Fantasy-style RPG.
Ys 1, 2, or 3                     More fantasy.

All these games have been translated to English. Try to get English versions,
because the Japanese originals are very hard to understand if you do not know
the language.

@{U}Shoot'em-ups@{UU}
Space Manbow       Great gameplay, great graphics, great music. The best.
Firebird           Another classic. Find map parts to open new sections.
Aleste 1 or 2      Great vertical shooters...
Nemesis 1, 2 or 3  ...and great horizontal ones...
Salamander         ...and another...
Parodius           ...and to top it off, a spoof Nemesis game!
Laydock            Terrific graphics, but a bit slow.
T.N.T.             More great graphics, but a bit unfriendly to control.
Undeadline         Rather difficult but very pretty.
Strategic Mars     Not very pretty, but compelling to play somehow.

Laydock was the first MSX2 game I ever saw, back in 1985. I was totally amazed
by the quality of the graphics, and even today they don't look that bad!

@{U}Puzzle games@{UU}
Eggerland Mystery 1 & 2  Hundreds of levels of puzzling pleasure.
Kings Valley 2           Fun puzzle game. Be sure to get the MSX2 version.

@{U}Miscellaneous@{UU}
F1 Spirit          Fun racing game.
Penguin Adventure  Unique adventure game, featuring penguins.
Feedback           Space Harrier-like game. Impressive stuff for MSX.
Firehawk           A transformer battles its way through a platform world.

@endnode

*****************************************************************

@node DISKGAMES "Disk games"
@{jcenter}@{fg highlight}Disk games@{fg text}
@{jleft}
These are games that fill one or more disks completely. They are usually for
MSX2, and often support the FM-Pac. Unfortunately they are almost always in
Japanese, and are impossible (or very hard) to play without knowledge of that
language.

The "Jap.?" column lists whether or not you can play the game if you do not
know Japanese. The following markings are used:

  Y = Knowledge of Japanese language is required.
  N = You can figure it out without having to know Japanese.
  E = You can play without knowing Japanese, but it is going to take some
      effort.

